explanation: The solution uses a breadth-first search (BFS) algorithm to explore the graph. It maintains a queue of nodes to visit, along with their distance from the starting node and the color of the last edge traversed. The algorithm iteratively dequeues nodes, updates the shortest path distances, and explores their neighbors, ensuring alternating edge colors. The use of a visited set prevents revisiting nodes, and the algorithm terminates when the target node is reached or all reachable nodes are explored.

